plotText.plainText: BoJack Horseman was the star of the hit television show "Horsin' Around" in the '80s and '90s, but now he's washed up, living in Hollywood, complaining about everything, and wearing colorful sweaters.

items.titleText: BoJack Horseman: The BoJack Horseman Story, Chapter One
items.plot: A publishing house eagerly awaits BoJack's memoirs, but he hasn't even started yet. His agent/ex and his publisher try to talk him into working with a ghost writer, but BoJack's too despondent about being washed up to focus.
BoJack gets into trouble after taking muffins a Navy Seal had "dibs" on and then calling American soldiers jerks on live television.
A child actress from the sitcom BoJack starred in 20 years ago shows up at his house leading to a series of chaotic events.

image.caption: Will Arnett, Paul F. Tompkins, Aaron Paul, Amy Sedaris, Alison Brie, and Wyatt Cenac in BoJack Horseman (2014)

items.plot: Bojack mentors Todd in his upcoming career; meanwhile Diane's ex-boyfriend writes an article about Mr. Peanutbutter for an online article.
A business trip for BoJack and Diane takes a detour; Todd runs a scam that gets him in trouble.
In a bout of drunken jealousy toward Mr. Peanutbutter, BoJack steals the "D" from the Hollywood sign for Diane. Meanwhile, Todd finds himself juggling two very demanding dates.
Princess Carolyn tries to have it all and prove she's the best agent in the biz, while Bojack, Todd, and Vanessa Gecko make it as difficult as possible.
When he learns his old friend from "Horsin' Around" is dying, BoJack tries to mend fences.
A love struck BoJack tries to sabotage a wedding; Todd accepts a surprising new professional role.
BoJack shoots a movie at Mr. Peanutbutter's house; Diane finishes her book.
BoJack embarks on a project in his typically gonzo style, leading to a drug-fueled revelation.
Months after his memoir is released, BoJack's being considered for a role that's a life long dream.
